Program: Discovery
Title: Venus - across the Sun
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrypx
Last Broadcast Date: 25 May 2004
Second of a two-part series on Venus as astronomers prepare to view a rare planetary event. Venus transits the Sun once every 100 years or so. This programme looks at some of the historical attempts to measure transits and the adventures that accompanied them.